file: crates/ctx-summarize/tests/summarize.rs
behavior: Integration tests for ctx-summarize's runner, Fs trait, and Agent trait, covering leaf-then-rollup summarization order, prompt/path/scope error gating, and real-subprocess Agent behavior via `sh`/`cat`.
edit_notes:
  - Defines FakeFs (in-memory BTreeMap-backed Fs impl) and RecordingAgent (records (system, user) call pairs, returns "SUMMARY[{system}]") used as test doubles; keep in sync with the real Fs and Agent trait signatures in ctx_summarize::fs / ctx_summarize::agent.
  - Asserts runner::run never writes intent.md, only .ctx files; asserts rollup write order is leaf-up (deepest dir first, root last).
  - Subprocess tests spawn literal shell commands ("cat", "exit 3", "true") via SubprocessAgent::new, relying on `sh` being present and requiring no network.
functions:
invariants:
  - runner::run writes leaves before rollups, and rollups in leaf-to-root order (child dirs before parents, root last).
  - runner::run never writes/modifies intent.md files.
  - runner::scope_check(n, approved) errs with SummError::ScopeTooLarge when n > MAX_TARGETS and approved is false; ok otherwise.
  - Paths containing ".." are rejected with SummError::PathEscape; missing prompt files yield SummError::MissingPrompt; secret-like targets (e.g. config/.env) yield SummError::AccessDenied.
external_deps:
  - ctx_summarize::agent::SubprocessAgent: spawns a real child shell process (via "sh") to test the production Agent implementation without network I/O.